The TV series "Legend of the Silk Road" forum, organized by Office of State Ethnic Affairs, and Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region Party Committee publicity department, was held in Beijing November 11, to discuss the enlightenment and experience of the successful drama.
Danzhu Angben, deputy director of Office of State Ethnic Affairs, and Li Xuejun, standing member of the Autonomous Region Party Committee, attended the forum and delivered speeches.
The TV series "Legend of the Silk Road" forum, organized by Office of State Ethnic Affairs, and Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region Party Committee publicity department, was held in Beijing November 11, 2015.
The TV series "Legend of the Silk Road" forum, organized by Office of State Ethnic Affairs, and Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region Party Committee publicity department, was held in Beijing November 11, 2015.
"Legend of the Silk Road" aired on CCTV-1 while China was celebrating the 60th anniversary of the founding of the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region. Produced by playwright Jing Yi, it is the first drama to reflect the industrial development of minority ethnic group since the founding of People's Republic of China. 
Producer of TV series "Legend of the Silk Road", Jing Yi, delivered speech on the forum, organized by Office of State Ethnic Affairs, and Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region Party Committee publicity department, November 11, 2015.
"Legend of the Silk Road" cast members are from multi-ethnic groups, they reflect the ethnic groups’ arts and the spirit of unity and cooperation, and created an excellent literary masterpiece.
"Legend of the Silk Road" received a lot of positive feedback from mainstream media and television audiences nationwide. It also led to a wave of Xinjiang tourism and improved links between the mainland and Xinjiang.
Experts have commented that the play reveals the Chinese Dream via the art of television. "Legend of the Silk Road" presents vivid stories, national characteristics, and beautiful costumes, and it has achieved a major breakthrough for Xinjiang-themed TV dramas.



